      • setChangeType

        void setChangeType(int flags)
        Searches for change sets containing a change matching any of the specified flags. Note that if setName or setItem are used, this restriction applies to the same change. Set to -1 if any change kind is supported
        Parameters:
        flags - a bitwise combination of the kind flags from IChange, or -1 if all change kinds are supported.

      • getChangeType

        int getChangeType()
        Returns a bitwise combination of the flags from IChange, indicating the types of permissible changes. Returns -1 if the change type is not being considered as part of the search criteria.
        Returns:
        a bitwise combination of kind flags from IChange

      • getSourceId

        UUID getSourceId()
        Returns the port id matched changesets must have as the original port source id or null if matched changesets don't have to match against port id.
        Returns:
        The port id matched changesets must have as the original port source id or null if matched changesets don't have to match against port id.

      • setSourceId

        void setSourceId(UUID value)
        Searches for change sets that have the given port id as the original source. The result will include the change set with the given id (if the original port source was a change set) along with any change sets that are direct or indirect ports from the original source.
        Parameters:
        value - the port id

      • matches

        boolean matches(IChangeSet cs)
        Returns true if the given changeset matches (or may match) the properties in this search criteria, false if not. In other words a false result indicates this changeset definitely does not match the criteria, however a true result means it may or may not match. This method may be used to quickly filter out changesets from consideration
        Parameters:
        cs - the changeset to check, must not be null.
